==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Peculate
<hw>Pec"u*late</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Peculated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Peculating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>peculatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>peculari</ets> to peculate, akin to
<ets>peculium</ets> private property. See <er>Peculiar</er>.]</ety>
<def>To appropriate to one's own use the property of the public; to
steal public moneys intrusted to one's care; to embezzle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An oppressive, . . . rapacious, and <qex>peculating</qex>
despotism.</q> <rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peculation</ent>⟦br⟧
